<br>
Yesterday, he got mad at me because I said I was going to quit EQ again.  I had taken 2 days off work this month just to play and it was starting to effect RL.  I had previously retired for 9 months.  He got extremely angry.  He and his &quot;wife&quot; helped me on two major quests which was very fun and appreciated.  He acted like I wasted his time when all i wanted to do was play a &quot;GAME&quot; with my best friend.  <br>
<br>
We grew up together playing D&amp;D or our version of it and have been through alot together.  For the most part of the last 4 years we watched our other best friend nearly destroy his life with this game.  And I never thought he would do it also but I was wrong.  <br>
<br>
In RL he has a beautiful son and a step daughter that he hardly sees and I bet hasnt talked to them in over 2 months because he doesnt have a phone.  <br>
<br>
The worst part is he could call the company he used to work for and get a job in a minute because he is a total genius.  They would probably give him a raise and hug him when he went back.  Sure he has his reasons but the truth is he is playing eq day and night.  <br>
<br>
I love this game and understand its an individuals choice to play or not.  I found myself spending at least 4 hours a day on this game known as evercrack.  Which is why i quit.  I saw the movie the Last Samuri and in it they said the word Bushido meant &quot;Live each breath of your life.&quot;  This I found to be beautiful and very educational which is why i am quiting EQ.  I wish all of you the best and hope MY BEST FRIEND looks at reality and comes back to it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Gowt Rottentoe the retired<br>
